unittitle_ssm: Rabbi Arthur Schneier Papers
abstract_ssm: The Rabbi Arthur Schneier Papers consists of materials created and collected by Rabbi Arthur Schneier over the course of his life as a rabbi and advocate for human rights. The material in the collection dates from 1942 to 2018 with the bulk of the material spanning from the 1970s to the mid 2010s. The content of the collection centers around Schneier's work as an internationally known rabbi and as the president of the Appeal of Conscience Foundation. The bulk of the material present in this collection includes: correspondence, photographs, images, press, clippings, memoranda, and  ephemera from various domestic and international events. The collection also contains a small amount of audiovisual material the bulk of which is audio cassette tapes containing recordings of various Appeal of Conscience Foundation events and conferences attended by the rabbi.
corpname_ssm: Tamiment Library and Robert F. Wagner Labor Archives
heading_ssm: Rabbi Arthur Schneier Papers
